[[File:Tatsusayama_Kofun_Aerial_photograph_2007.jpg|thumb|Aerial view of Tatsusayama Kofun (2007)<br /><small>{{National Land Aerial Photograph}}</small>]]
Tatsusayama Kofun (竜佐山古墳) is a [[kofun]] located in Daisen Nakamachi, [[Sakai Ward]], [[:en:Sakai City|Sakai City]], [[:en:Osaka Prefecture|Osaka Prefecture]], within Daisen Park. It is part of the [[Mozu Tombs|Mozu Kofun Group]] and considered an accompanying tomb of the [[Daisenryō Kofun]] (Mausoleum of Emperor Nintoku). It is registered as part of the [[Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group|Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group - Ancient Kofun Clusters of Japan]], a [[:en:World Heritage Site|World Heritage Site]] for cultural properties.

== Overview ==
The keyhole-shaped kofun, oriented with its front section to the west, lies near the outer moat on the southern side of the Daisenryō Kofun. Its axis is parallel to the southern outer moat of the Daisenryō Kofun<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/911/00000146 |title=Tatsusayama Kofun / World Heritage Component / National Historic Site Database |accessdate=2022-08-04 |publisher=Cultural Affairs Agency}}</ref>{{Sfn|Kofun Cluster|2014|p=21}}. Historical maps from 1730 refer to it as "Ryōsayama," and early Shōwa period records indicate it was once called "Ryūsayama"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.city.sakai.lg.jp/kanko/hakubutsukan/collection/mozukofungun/kofun.html |title=Tatsusayama Kofun - Imperial Detached Area "Rogō" - Daisen Nakamachi / Mausoleum of Emperor Nintoku Kofun Encyclopedia |accessdate=2022-08-04 |publisher=Sakai City Museum}}</ref>. The mound measures 61 m in length, with the rear mound measuring 43 m in diameter and 8 m in height. The front section is 26 m wide and 2 m high{{Sfn|Kofun Cluster|2014|p=21}}.

== area ==
The area of the kofun are as follows{{Sfn|Kofun Cluster|2014|p=21}}:

* Mound Length: 61 m
* Rear Mound:
** Diameter: 43 m
** Height: 8 m
* Front Section:
** Width: 26 m
** Height: 2 m

== Historic Site ==

=== Sakai City Designated Historic Site ===
designation1: Moat of Tatsusayama Kofun. Designated on April 11, 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.city.sakai.lg.jp/kanko/rekishi/bunkazai/bunkazai/shokai/bunya/shiseki/tatsusayama.html |title=Tatsusayama Kofun Moat |accessdate=2022-08-04 |publisher=Sakai City Office Cultural Affairs Bureau designation1 Section}}</ref>.

== World Heritage ==
On July 6, 2019, the kofun was registered as part of the World Historic Site Site Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group - Ancient Kofun Clusters of Japan<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/special_content/hlinkJ |title=World Heritage / Historic Site Online |accessdate=2022-08-04 |publisher=Cultural Affairs Agency}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/901/00000020 |title=World Heritage / Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group - Ancient Kofun Clusters of Japan |accessdate=2022-08-04 |publisher=Cultural Affairs Agency}}</ref>.

== Access ==
* By train: Approximately 11 minutes on foot from [[:en:JR|JR]] [[:en:Hanwa Line|Hanwa Line]] [[:en:Uenoshiba Station|Uenoshiba Station]]
* By bus: From [[:en:Nankai Kōya Line|Nankai Kōya Line]] [[Sakai Higashi Station]], take a bus to Horiue Ryokumachi Itchō or Higashiyama Shako-mae and get off at Nankyō-dō Yonchō. Walk 5 minutes.

